    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, i guess. but it feels like there's a bit of a distinction missing there. like, even the \"good\" kind of nationalism often relies on drawing lines between \"us\" and \"them,\" right? isn't the very act of prioritizing one nation over others fundamentally a step toward the more dangerous stuff you mentioned? it seems hard to separate the two.",
