      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The distinction between civic and ethnic nationalism is crucial because it dictates whether the prioritization is inclusive or exclusive. Civic nationalism, which emphasizes shared adherence to democratic principles and the rule of law, is the only viable framework for a stable, modern state. To argue that *any* nationalism inevitably leads to global instability ignores the legitimate need for sovereign self-governance and cultural preservation. The danger arises only when that national identity is weaponized to justify oppression, not when it is used to build a functioning society.",
